{"id":"project-LICHEN-om93","title":"BLE transport: callbacks access transport_state after disconnect could race","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/ble_ipsp_transport.c
Lines: 97-140, 142-161

The BLE callbacks access transport_state.config.user_ctx without synchronization:

In connected_cb():
    if (transport_state.config.conn_cb) {
        transport_state.config.conn_cb(LICHEN_BLE_CONNECTED,
                                       transport_state.config.user_ctx);
    }

In disconnected_cb():
    if (transport_state.config.conn_cb) {
        transport_state.config.conn_cb(LICHEN_BLE_DISCONNECTED,
                                       transport_state.config.user_ctx);
    }

If the transport is deinitialized while a BLE connection/disconnection is in progress:
1. Deinit could clear config or free user_ctx
2. Callback fires and reads stale config pointer
3. user_ctx points to freed memory -> use-after-free

While deinit calls transport_stop() first, the BLE stack callbacks are asynchronous and may fire after stop() returns.

Fix: Check transport_state.initialized before invoking user callbacks, or copy callbacks/ctx under mutex before invoking.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:55:12.925939Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:55:12.92598Z"}

